# UI Quality Baseline

- Build mobile-first layouts, then scale up for tablet and desktop breakpoints.
- Keep heading hierarchy semantic and preserve keyboard-accessible interactions.
- Ensure form elements have clear labels, validation states, and error messaging.
- Maintain sufficient color contrast and visible focus states on interactive elements.
- Reuse behavior and accessibility primitives, but keep each app's visual expression independent.
- Use semantic tokens/utilities; app themes own final color, typography, and style identity.
- Use performant media defaults: responsive sizes, lazy loading where appropriate.
